Etymology. This species is dedicated to Prof. Seiji Goshima, Faculty of Fisheries Sciences, Hokkaido University, Japan , who has greatly contributed to biological studies of the new species ( Niu & Fuji 1989 ;
Niu et al . 1992
, 1994a , b , 1997 , 1998 ).

The reproductive cycle of the species (as
Collisella heroldi
) was examined by Niu & Fuji (1989) . According to this study, the reproductive season is August to October, and size at maturity is about 5 mm .
